The Article 11 of the First Company Law Directive requires that:
- The company's statutes must be drawn up in accordance with European Union law, including Articles 27 to 30 (the "EU Statute") or any other applicable EU legislation;
- Any amendment made by the shareholders meeting shall not affect the validity of the original document unless it is expressly provided for otherwise;
- Shareholder meetings may only adopt resolutions on matters which fall within their competence under national law;
- A copy of each decision taken at an ordinary general assembly

The European Union's Charter of Fundamental Rights is one such treaty that provides protection for both the freedom of establishment (the right to establish businesses in another country) and the freedom to provide services within the EU, which includes:
- The free movement of goods, persons, services, capital, and workers across borders;
- Protection against discrimination based on nationality or membership in an ethnic group;
- Respect for private property rights;
- Freedom from arbitrary arrest or detention;
- Right to legal remedies when violated by public authorities;
- Prohibition
